	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hmmm the stat debate over rogues is long and twisted. While strength inevitably comes in to play when calculating damage it is important to remember that the ethos of the rogue is to strike successfully as much as possible and to not be struck at all. The stats involved in determining the above are ac,dex and agi. My rogue only has a stength of 75 but at lvl 10 will BS for 25. It has been said that the formula for BS includes the element str+bs skill. If this is true then the favorable stat to raise would be BS skill as this will eventually surpass, numerically, your strength stat. So you want to raise BS skill as quickly as possible. As rogue skills are determined by agi and dex it makes sense that to enable faster skill rise, dumping points into agi and dex would be the way to go. But at higher lvls, where skill caps are reached, a higher strength stat would be preferable.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
