	   <tr><td colspan=2>rogues are not meant for soloing... but what they are meant for is small groups. a great method that has worked in my experience is to find a single partner to hunt with in large outdoors zones (like in kunark). now, it's difficult to find a druid or necromancer partner because they can just solo, and don't want to lose any exp... but a good partner, surprisingly, and someone who will always want a group, is another rogue. <br>i'm sure you're all familiar with ping pong. well, throw in that instill doubt (with double chance for success), and an SBD (come on, one of you is bound to have one of these suckers... at least on vallon, everyone does), and you've got a snared, feared mob that's getting double-backstabbed. it doesn't get much nicer than that. even in the worst case (it isn't snared or feared), you still have two people taking the damage instead of one, and you're still landing a consistent backstab (two rogues can sponge more damage than one warrior if you ping pong properly and have halfway decent armor). <br>for those of you who don't know ping pong: have a rogue on either side of the mob. you backstab, your partner evades. mob turns to you, and you evade while your partner backstabs. <br>this works great in my experience... then again, what do I know, I'm just a rogue. <br><br>Kryven Cyclone &lt;Order of the Black Rose&gt;<br>29th season Assassin, Vallon Zek<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
