	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've played pingpong with another rogue in BB - lol, its funny.&nbsp;&nbsp;Backstabs coming from both sides consecutively(when the mob spins to turn to the first BS) really seems to confuse the heck out of the monster, and ends up spending most of his time from then on turning around and around, despite if its just a regular hit from the backside, lol.  It was really entertaining to both of us rogues. <br><br>     Im finding out that tanks that dont like to solo can learn to really value a rogue on the backside of a monster, who's twice more effective than a tank on the backside.<br>Ive been very successful just with a tank partnership - they seem to live to take on the damage as long as you do a very good job tearing up the backside of a mob.  You hardly get attack, considering the heavier hits are consistently coming from the tank that keeps the mob's attention.  But the big BS - tanks just luv dat!  And you can hide and pull away when you do get attacked.  And by then, you got another BS clear on your hot key!<br><br>    I was soloing a whole camp of bandits - hehe, pretty easy once you hit 20, they dont like to aggro you.  I was bored waiting for spawning and decided to run over the top of a teepee.  Couple times and i was picking up safefall, lol.  On my spare time i spent running TP's and maxing out safefall at my level pretty quickly.  No chance of being hurt - can be repeated every second!  <br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
