	   <tr><td colspan=2>hmm....<br><br>maybe this would be true if Verant had designed rogues properly. The things you said vaguely make sense, but what does a rogue become, as a solo, after that first backstab? A monk. not only a monk, but a monk with no special attack, less hitpoints, and no ability to mend or feign death. Sure, they have Instill Doubt, but a necromancer can fear a mob with much more precision. I know druids and necros who have found it EASY to solo beyond 50 - so easy, in fact, that they prefer soloing over groups. I'm not saying rogues should have these abilities, rather I'm saying that a rogue can't solo. obviously you don't have any experience playing a rogue beyond level 35 if you honestly believe that a rogue can solo its way to 50. It can't. no rogue can solo beyond 35 without extreme difficulty, and, though i've never even seen it attempted, I'm sure no rogue could solo beyond 40 at all.<br><br>perhaps playing a blue server, where every piece of equipment on a newbie comes from high level zones around the world, these things are possible, but certainly not on my server. try soloing a rogue up to level 18 with leather armor and giant snake fangs. <br><br>I don't mind your ignorance, but don't let "I can solo MY rogue to 50 because that guy said so" be the death of these innocent budding rogues. <br><br>my method works reliably over soloing, in my own experience. if you have another method, you're welcome to try... just don't flame me when I'm the one who survives the battles. <br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
