	   <a name=97426137926368></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97426137926368><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=97426137926368>Almost EVERYTHING</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=97426137926368#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2379><span id= >Vincit</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>7 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Nov 14th 11:09 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2><br>Well, I'm only 18th level, so I'm sure there are others wiser in the way of the Rogue than I.&nbsp;&nbsp;Having said that, I'll offer my own thoughts on rogues anyhow.<br><br>First and foremost, try keeping up with both 1HS and Piercing for melee purposes.  You never know when a cool new weapon may come out that you just *have* to use.  A rogue should be flexible, so practice, practice, practice.  Besides, there are a lot of 1HS weapons with nifty procs, so you'll want some skill there for when using them in your offhand later in life.  We all know that we have to have a piercing in the primary hand for backstabbing purposes, so keeping THAT skill maxxed is a must.<br><br>Second, Hiding Moving Silently are a rogue's boon companions; practice these every level right off the bat until you max it for the level.  Same goes for Sense Heading, just keep practicing them and they'll all go up in due time.<br><br>Since Hide is the real skill used for Evade, make sure you max it every level.  Remember, you must STOP your auto attack to use Hide to Evade.<br><br>Picking Pockets is one of those skills that can really tick off a group.  I will tell people that I'm practicing Picking Pockets on a Mob, then every once in a while I'll share out my loot with the group.  If the group says they don't want me to pick, I don't pick.  Or I offer the counter of using Pick Pockets as a taunt only in emergencies.  Also, I'm the type of rogue who is not above giving away things I can't use to others.  Casters (especially clerics) love getting extra odds and ends (especially gems for certain spells.)  They remember who gave them the gems, too; which comes in handy for you at later levels.<br><br>Backstabbing is a great skill, but it's pretty hard to raise up due to the time it takes to do multiple attacks.  Unless you really work at it with a group that wants to help, it can take a long time for Backstab to rise up to high levels.<br><br>SafeFall is one of those skills that is often underused.  I've heard you used to be able to trick monsters into falling off cliffs and getting hurt, but that this has been nerfed.  I haven't been around long enough to know for sure.  I do know that being able to run off cliffs while taking minor damage (or none) has saved me more than once, as it gets me a lead on the chasing monster.  THAT can give me a crucial chance to zone if need be.<br><br>Now, as to the Archery vs. Throwing debate, remember when I mentioned keeping casters happy?  I don't pay for arrows or throwing daggers.  I get magic ones summoned for me by people whom I've given things I didn't need.  Makes the skills cheap to practice.  So, as with 1HS and Piercing, I try to keep both up.  Currently, I'm maxxed with both skills.<br><br>As you might guess, I'm a social rogue.  I much prefer a group than soloing, and will gladly give up a bit of loot to casters in order to be part of a well oiled group.  Because of this, I'm often buffed up, well healed and well fed by others.  Sure, you get less exp per Mob in a group, but you can kill so much more in a given time frame you'll get more out of a group than alone.  Plus, you'll spend less time looking for your corpse if the worst happens.<br><br>I'll leave my thoughts on which weapons and gear is best for a later post.<br><br>Safe Trails,<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Vincit Scoundrel<br>Knave of Hearts</td></tr>
