	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96836238816763><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=96836238816763>RE: Half Elf Rogues Disadvantaged?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=96836238816763#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Sep 7th 5:33 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I play a half-elf rogue and I haven't found too many disadvantages.&nbsp;&nbsp;Their stats are middle of the road, but they have higher natural dex/agi than humans.  They don't have any special abilities like forage or slam, but they at least have infravision.  I've found the biggest downfall is that, like humans, they can only wear medium size things.  Most newbie zones have at least wolves or bears in them (in Halas you can have full PW armor by lvl 3!), but none have cats so getting non-twinked early armor is harder.<br><br>Other than that they have good beginning int. and charisma which is good for buying/selling.  I like my half-elf rogue...no complaints here.  Also, they seem to have decent faction in all the rogue guilds I've been to.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
