	   <tr><td colspan=2>Fight as many low blues as you can. As you get higher you'll spend enough fighting that offense should raise pretty easily, but at lower levels it is a problem because you level so quickly that you don't keep up. Solution? Fight low blues. The smaller experience will give you more time to fight, which equals more time to max out that offense. Oh and for reference I'm assuming that you're still low level when I'm saying this. But don't worry, up to around the double digits at least I'd venture to say that everyone is playing catch up on skills. Every caster I've made I've had to designate time just to catch up on the different spell categories (my cleric just finally maxed out divination at level 20 lol).<br>Good luck!<br><br>Dagis<br>Midget cleric on Tarew Marr that figures he should finally register his name so that every post he makes isn't auto set as "poor".<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
